    <header>
        <h1>Standardized Analytics Framework Proposal</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">Consolidating business analytics requests to create efficiency, consistency, and a single source of truth</div>
        <div class="subtitle">Document ID: SAF-PROP-2023-001 | Version: 1.0 | Date: <span id="current-date"></span></div>
    </header>
    

    
    <section id="current-challenges">
        <h2>2. Current Challenges</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Inefficiency:</strong> Engineering and data teams frequently handle manual, repetitive requests for similar data points.</li>
            <li><strong>Inconsistency:</strong> Different teams may receive slightly different figures for the same metric due to varying extraction methods.</li>
            <li><strong>Lack of Visibility:</strong> Stakeholders often do not know what data is available or who to ask, leading to delayed decision-making.</li>
            <li><strong>Security/Compliance Risk:</strong> Ad-hoc data exports increase the risk of data mishandling or inconsistent audit trails.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section id="proposed-solution">
        <h2>3. Proposed Solution: The "Standardized Analytics Framework"</h2>
        <p>Our goal is to move from ad-hoc requests to a structured, self-service model.</p>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Initiative</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                    <th>Benefit</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Centralized Data Intake</strong></td>
                    <td>Implement the proposed form template (Reference: Q1b Identification) as the sole input method for new data requests.</td>
                    <td>Single source of requirements, clearer prioritization.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Standardized Metric Definitions</strong></td>
                    <td>Define and document a consistent definition for common metrics (e.g., "Monthly Active User," "Premium Asset Count").</td>
                    <td>Ensures data consistency and trust in reporting.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Tiered Delivery System</strong></td>
                    <td>Implement a tiered approach to data delivery:</td>
                    <td>Aligns delivery method with urgency/audience.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Tier 1: Self-Service UI Dashboard</strong></td>
                    <td>For high-demand, high-frequency metrics (User stats, Consumption).</td>
                    <td>Empowers stakeholders with real-time access; reduces engineering burden.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Tier 2: Standardized Export API/Tool</strong></td>
                    <td>For data exports (Audit logs, billing data) that require scheduled or manual download but adhere to a standard format.</td>
                    <td>Secure, consistent data exportation mechanism.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><strong>Exclude Internal DevOps Metrics</strong></td>
                    <td>Scope this project only for business/user-facing metrics. System performance metrics will remain with DevOps monitoring tools.</td>
                    <td>Clear project scope; prevents overlap with existing monitoring tools.</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </section>
    
    <section id="resources-timeline">
        <h2>4. Required Resources and Timeline</h2>
        <p>We require approval to allocate <strong>[X] engineering days</strong> and coordination time from the assigned team members over the next <strong>[Y] weeks</strong> to implement this framework.</p>
        
